The finality of the solution proposed by Speke to the “Nile question” was questioned by his partner Richard Francis Burton. The dispute between Speke and Burton was resolved in favor of the first only in 1871, when journalist Henry Morton Stanley examined the headwaters of the White Nile in the Ripon Falls area[en]. from the sources of the Nile was discovered in 1937 by the German traveler Burchard Waldecker [en] - originating at the foot of Mount Kikizi (Burundi), it is part of the water system of the Kagera River, which flows into Lake Victoria. In 1950-1951, Jean Laporte's expedition was able to swim for the first time the entire river from the source, where Waldecker built a symbolic pyramid in 1938, to the mouth. The Nile flows from south to north.